    <main>
        <h1>LeetCode 1545: Find Kth Bit in Nth Binary String (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                Given two positive integers n and k, the binary string Sn is formed as follows: S1 = "0", Si = Si-1 +
                "1" + reverse(invert(Si-1)) for i &gt; 1. Return the kth bit in Sn. It is guaranteed that k is valid for
                the given n. Note that invert(x) inverts all the bits in x (0 changes to 1 and 1 changes to 0), and
                reverse(x) reverses the string x.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: n = 3, k = 1<br>
                Output: "0"<br>
                Explanation: S3 = "0111001". The 1st bit is "0".
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    char findKthBit(int n, int k) {
        int inv = 0; // count of flips
        while (n &gt; 1) {
            int len = (1 &lt;&lt; n) - 1;
            int mid = len / 2 + 1;
            if (k == mid)
                return (inv % 2) ? '0' : '1';
            if (k &gt; mid) {             // go to mirrored section
                k = (1 &lt;&lt; (n - 1)) - (k - mid);
                inv++;
            }
            n--;
        }
        return (inv % 2) ? '1' : '0';
    }
};</code></pre>
